D. Schnitzer, Appellee, v. John Kramer, Appellant.Gen. No. 19,948.

(Not to be reported in full.)

Appeal from the Circuit Court of Cook county; the Hon. John A. Dowdall, Judge, presiding. Heard in this court at the October term, 1913.Affirmed.Opinion filed October 13, 1914.

Statement of the Case.

This case involved the same facts and the questions presented for determination were the same as those considered in Schnitzer v. Kramer, ante, p. 350, and the decision in that case held conclusive.

Thomas W. Reilly, for appellant.Sonnenschein, Berkson & Fishell, for appellee. Mr. Justice McSurely

delivered the opinion of the court.
